ACT:
 U.P. Urban Areas Zamindari Abolition and Land Reforms Act, 1956--Land leased for planting a grove, erecting buildings etc.--Does not fall exclusively under s. 2(1)(d)-Section 2(1)(d) must be interpreted as relating to agricultural land only--Thus construed if protected by Art. 31A of the Constitution--Land in question not proved to be 'agricultural area'--Notification under s. 8 of Act cannot be issued in respect of it--Abatement of suits and appeals under Rule 39 of the U.P. Urban Areas Zamindari Abolition and Land Reforms Rules 1957.
 
